---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Disclaimer"
  description="Medical disclaimer for IsItAuDHD.com quizzes and content. Our quizzes are not diagnostic tools."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-8">Disclaimer</h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-text-light leading-relaxed">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-3">Not a Diagnostic Tool</h2>
        <p>
          The quizzes and assessments on IsItAuDHD.com are for <strong class="text-text">informational
          and self-exploration purposes only</strong>. They are not diagnostic tools and cannot
          replace a professional clinical evaluation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-3">Not Medical Advice</h2>
        <p>
          The content on this website does not constitute medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.
          Always seek the advice of a qualified healthcare provider with any questions you may
          have regarding a medical condition. Never disregard professional medical advice or delay
          in seeking it because of something you have read on this website.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-3">Quiz Results</h2>
        <p>
          Quiz results are generated by an algorithm based on your self-reported responses.
          They reflect patterns in your answers, not a clinical assessment of your
          neurodevelopmental profile. High scores do not mean you have autism, ADHD, or AuDHD.
          Low scores do not mean you don't.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-3">Seek Professional Help</h2>
        <p>
          If you believe you may be autistic, have ADHD, or have both, we encourage you to
          seek a formal evaluation from a psychologist, psychiatrist, or other qualified
          professional who has experience with neurodivergence in adults. A professional
          can provide a thorough assessment that accounts for your full history and
          presentation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-3">Accuracy</h2>
        <p>
          While we strive to base our content on current research, neurodivergence is a
          rapidly evolving field. Information on this site may not reflect the most recent
          findings. We make no warranties about the completeness, reliability, or accuracy
          of this information.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-3">Crisis Resources</h2>
        <p>
          If you are in crisis or need immediate help, please contact:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li><strong class="text-text">988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline:</strong> Call or text 988 (US)</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text">Crisis Text Line:</strong> Text HOME to 741741</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text">Emergency:</strong> Call 911 or your local emergency number</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
